      "writtenOn": "2018-10-18T09:38:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I started removing the subpixel feature from 4fLinear, but then I realized it\u0027s not just visual candy: with the interval-burst approach, there\u0027s an attack vector where one can lock up the thread for arbitrary duration by passing in super-tiny gradients (which produce close-to-zero advance/progress).\n\nThis defends against that scenario: https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/skia/src/shaders/gradients/Sk4fLinearGradient.cpp?rcl\u003d198b87e5be2083d15901a91c82caad1912e8209a\u0026l\u003d299\n\nIIRC we added that code because cluster-fuzz found the attack.\n\nMaybe there\u0027s another solution, but if we\u0027re going to apply special treatment to squashed gradients, drawing the color average seems the only reasonable outcome.",
      "parentUuid": "e83c7adf_f1fda9c3",
      "revId": "4eb3b6c85fb1a77d0a641f7eba6651463d5fd09c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
